<section xml:id="section-q1-large">
  <title>Large Dataset</title>

<paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large">
    <title>Question 1 - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You arrive just before planting. The air is dry and hot, and farmers are already gathering in the shade. One of the farmers spots you, and comes running over.
    </p>
        <image source="images/aminou_question.png" width="70%">
          <description>A farmer eagerly approaching Aminou before the study begins, asking which variety to plant for the upcoming season</description>
        </image>
    <p>
      <q>Aminou! Thank goodness you're here. We've heard about your big study across the three countries. Everyone says you now have real evidence. So tell me - what variety should I plant?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You pause. Across Ilam, Regin, and Anikrub, thousands of plots were studied. Farmers tried two varieties: ICRI and Locale.
    </p>

    <p>
      You have the data and so you sit down with them to give them some advice. What do you say?
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>Choose your answer:</alert>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-either">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
</paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri">
    <title>ICRI - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You nod confidently, <q>Plant ICRI.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer squints at you, <q>Hmm.</q> They're not convinced, and that plays on your mind.
    </p>

    <p>
      Later that evening, as you sit reviewing the data more carefully, something unsettles you.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>Wait<ellipsis/> what?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You flip back through your tables.
    </p>

    <p>
      You would have expected that pattern somewhere else -- but do you expect that here in Anikrub?
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer comes back the next day.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>So<ellipsis/> are you sure?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      What do you say now?
    </p>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-either">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri-icri">
    <title>ICRI Again - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You double down, <q>Still ICRI.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer raises an eyebrow, <q>Do you work for this ICRI variety or something?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You feel your face warm. That Anikrub sun is hot today.
    </p>

    <p>
      Time to slow down.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Have you looked at yield by region and variety?
      </p>
      <p>
        Not just overall yield - but yield broken down by region as well as variety.
      </p>
      <p>
        The data are not flat, they are layered. Try again.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri-regin">
    <title>Incorrect Region</title>
    
    <p>
      <q>Regin, of course.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer frowns, <q>That doesn't sound very confident.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The Anikrub sun is hot and you feel sweat going down your face. You realise you may be smoothing over something important.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Look at yield by region and variety. Averages across countries can hide regional differences.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri-ilam">
    <title>Incorrect Region</title>
    
    <p>
      <q>Ilam, of course.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer frowns, <q>That doesn't sound very confident.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The Anikrub sun is hot and you feel sweat going down your face. You realise you may be smoothing over something important.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Look at yield by region and variety. Averages across countries can hide regional differences.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri-either">
    <title>Either - Large Dataset (After ICRI)</title>
    
    <p>
      <q>Either one should be fine.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer frowns, <q>That doesn't sound very confident.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The Anikrub sun is hot and you feel sweat going down your face. You realise you may be smoothing over something important.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Look at yield by region and variety. Averages across countries can hide regional differences.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-icri-idk">
    <title>I Don't Know - Large Dataset (After ICRI)</title>
    
    <p>
      You hesitate. <q>I<ellipsis/> need to check something.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You reopen your analysis.
    </p>

    <p>
      You suddenly notice that you've been looking at overall averages across all three countries.
    </p>

    <p>
      But this farmer is in Anikrub, and the pattern here is not the same as the overall pattern from your data.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint:
      </p>
      <p>
        Filter the data to Anikrub.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then compare yield by variety.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-locale">
    <title>Locale - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You say confidently, <q>Locale.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer smiles. <q>Interesting. That matches what some of us have seen.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      But then he tilts his head. <q>If you're so sure<ellipsis/> tell me this. In which region does Local outperform ICRI on average?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      Now it's your turn to think.
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>Option:</alert>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-regin">Regin</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-ilam">Ilam</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Anikrub</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-locale-correct">
    <title>Locale - Anikrub (Correct)</title>
    
    <p>
      You smile. <q>For Anikrub? Plant the Local variety.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer nods slowly. <q>That makes sense. It's what many of us have been noticing.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You feel relieved -- and slightly humbled.
    </p>

    <p>
      Across the entire dataset, ICRI may look stronger on average. But when you break the data down by region, Anikrub tells a different story.
    </p>

    <p>
      You've just discovered something important:
    </p>

    <p>
      Overall averages can mislead and the best decision can depend on context.
    </p>

    <p>
      You turn the page in your notebook. This is more complicated than you thought.
    </p>

    <p>
      Continue to <xref ref="Q2-large">Question 2</xref>.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-either">
    <title>Either - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      <q>Either one.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer looks disappointed, <q>That's not very helpful.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You may be flattening the data too much.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        <alert>Advice:</alert>
      </p>
      <p>
        Break down yield by variety.
      </p>
      <p>
        The story changes when you disaggregate.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      Go back to <xref ref="Q1-large">Question 1</xref>.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-idk">
    <title>I Don't Know - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You stall.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>Well<ellipsis/> it sure is lovely weather here in Anikrub today.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer laughs.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>You statisticians.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You realise avoidance won't help.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        <alert>Advice:</alert>
      </p>
      <p>
        Start by comparing average yield by variety.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then break it down by region. This should lead you to your answer
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-icri-either">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-large-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-large-help">
    <title>Help - Large Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      Let's walk through this carefully.
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>Step 1:</alert> Look at overall average yield by variety. You may find that ICRI looks better overall.
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>Step 2:</alert> Now break the data down by region. When you look at Anikrub specifically, Local outperforms ICRI on average.
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>What happened?</alert>
    </p>

    <p>
      This is an example of how aggregated data can hide regional differences. The distribution of varieties across regions affects the overall average.
    </p>

    <p>
      Never give advice based only on overall averages when context matters.
    </p>

    <p>
      For Anikrub, the correct answer is: <alert>Locale</alert>
    </p>

    <p>
      Go to <xref ref="Q2-large">Question 2</xref>.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

</section>
